cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.AI

The paper describes a client-server architecture for solving multiple learning tasks from distributed datasets while preserving privacy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as well as distributed computing (cs.DC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a common database also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the use of regularization and kernel methods suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
